                },
                {
                    "id" : "introduction",
                    "text" : [ 
                               { "text" : "### Introduction\n\nFrequently, when performing addition, we respond automatically—a habit that leads us to reflect",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": ":"
                               },
                               { "text" : "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: What is the actual result?</b><br /><br />When we add two numbers, do we always obtain the same outcome?<br /><br />For example: what is the result of 40 + 40?</div></div></center></p>",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "html",
                                 "PostMention": " "
                               },
                               { "text" : "If you concluded that the answer is 80, you are likely correct. However, we cannot rule out the possibility of error, as we have only provided the numbers without specifying what is being added",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id" : "always",
                    "text" : [ 
                               { "text" : "### When Is 40 + 40 Equal to 80?\n\nThe question in this section’s title invites further reflection",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": ":"
                               },
                               { "text" : "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 2: Where Can We Apply This?</b><br /><br />Can you identify scenarios where 40 + 40 results in 80?</div></div></center></p>",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "html",
                                 "PostMention": " "
                               },
                               { "text" : "Let us observe our hands once again",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": ":"
                               },
                               { "text" : "<p><table class=\"book_navigation\"><tr><td>Left hand</td><td>Right hand</td></tr><tr><td><img id=\"imgLH\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgLH', '0%')\" src=\"images/Left_Hand.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/></td><td><img id=\"imgRH\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgRH', '0%')\" src=\"images/Right_Hand.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Figure 1: Hands reprsentation. The source codes are available in project GitHub (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('240800f3-ede4-4deb-9d4e-915a3a03fa68'); return false;\">History Tracers Team, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, Source code</a>)</td></tr></table></p>",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "html",
                                 "PostMention": " "
                               },
                               { "text" : "If we combine 40 fingers and add another 40 fingers, we would ultimately obtain 80 fingers. A similar result would occur if we performed the counting using hands. However, this concept is not limited to the human body—we can also apply this type of summation to trees and other animals. Reflecting on these examples, let us consider another question",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": ":"
                               },
                               { "text" : "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\">?</i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 3: What Is the Common Element?</b><br /><br />Can you identify something that connects us to plants and other animals?</div></div></center></p>",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "html",
                                 "PostMention": " "
                               },
                               { "text" : "Like other animals and plants, we are living beings (or, if you prefer, natural beings). The same applies to the numbers we have used so far. These natural numbers, represented in mathematics by the symbol ℕ, are directly tied to our understanding of counting",
                                 "source" : [
                                 ],
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               },
                               { "text" : "Within the context of natural numbers, it is correct to state that 40 + 40 = 80, provided we are referring to the same entities (whether objects or living beings). Nevertheless, it is crucial to analyze the context and its dimensions, as we will explore further",
                                 "source" : [
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "0db84048-6184-4412-b538-0c41c6f8438e",
                                                "text": "McDonough, M.",
                                                "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2025", "month" : "2", "day" : "26" }},
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "ea43d68d-8004-4fa8-bf58-82b57a6458ae",
                                                "text": "Weisstein, Eric W."}
                                 ],
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id" : "dimensions",
                    "text" : [ 
                               { "text" : "### Dimensions\n\n#### Analysis of Dimensional Summation\n\nWhen summing natural elements, we must consider more than just the numerical values. It is essential to understand exactly what quantities we are summing—meaning we need to verify the dimensions of the objects involved",
                                 "source" : [
                                              { "type": 0,
                                                "uuid": "36b5573f-d92a-461c-afb9-ade2ad1ac0c2",
                                                "text": "Cambridge Dictionary, dimension"}
                                 ],
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               },
                               { "text" : "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 4: Dimensionless Summation</b><br /><br />What is the result of adding 40 bananas + 40 apples? Could we obtain 80 grapes as the final result?</div></div></center></p>",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "html",
                                 "PostMention": " "
                               },
                               { "text" : "This reflection demonstrates a case where 40 + 40 does not equal 80. As observed, the initial question failed to properly account for dimensional consistency.\n\nA valid correction would be to group the items as fruits rather than as distinct species. Thus, when summing 40 fruits + 40 fruits, we obtain 80 fruits—a logically consistent result.\n\nWe conclude that while dimensional analysis does not verify calculation accuracy, it reveals whether we are making a fundamental categorical error",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               },
                               { "text" : "#### I only know, I do not know\n\nLet us gather two glasses of water (40 mL/1.35 oz each), an empty jar, and a thermometerr",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               },
                               { "text" : "<p><table class=\"book_navigation\"><tr><td>Empty Jar</td><td>Thermometer</td><td>Two glasses</td></tr><tr><td><i class=\"fa-solid fa-jar\" style=\"font-size:6em\"></i></td><td><i class=\"fa-solid fa-thermometer-half\" style=\"font-size:3em\"></i></td><td><i class=\"fa-solid fa-whiskey-glass\" style=\"font-size:3em\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-whiskey-glass\" style=\"font-size:3em\"></i></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"3\">Chart 1: Experimental setup illustration. Images available in Font Awesome's free version (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('ad0cdae3-2260-4462-86a7-0987c6ffc82b'); return false;\">Font Awesome</a>).</td></tr></table></p>",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "html",
                                 "PostMention": " "
                               },
                               { "text" : "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_lab_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_lab question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-microscope\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_lab\"><b>Practice 1: Laboratory of Summation</b><br /><br />Measure the water temperature in both glasses (assume 40°C/104°F on a hot day).<br /><br />Carefully pour the water into the jar (total: 80 mL/2.7 oz).<br /><br />Remeasure the temperature in the jar. You will observe that the temperature remains 40°C/104°F.</div></div></p>",
                                 "source" : null,
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "html",
                                 "PostMention": " "
                               },
                               { "text" : "The combined water maintains the same temperature, demonstrating that temperature follows different summation rules than volume",
                                 "source" : [
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "b8da01e6-1f56-4677-86cf-5153fe47f501",
                                                "text": "Hossenfelder, Sabine",
                                                "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2022", "month" : "2", "day" : "26" }}
                                 ],
                                 "isTable" : false,
                                 "date_time" : null,
                                 "format" : "markdown",
                                 "PostMention": "."
                               }
                    ]
